  "prompt": "If I am talking on whatsapp call to someone and another person calls me on my whatsapp. what status will he get. will it show busy?",
  "response": "When you're engaged in a WhatsApp call and someone else tries to call you on WhatsApp, the experience for the second caller generally mirrors the behavior of being \"busy.\" Here's what typically happens:\n\n1. **Incoming Call During an Active Call:**\n   - **Caller Experience:** The person attempting to call you will see your phone ring, but since you're already on a call, you won't be able to answer the new incoming call immediately.\n   - **Notification:** Depending on WhatsApp's current implementation and updates, the caller might receive a notification indicating that you're already on another call or simply experience the call not connecting until you're available.\n\n2. **Call Handling:**\n   - **Queueing Calls:** WhatsApp does not support multiple simultaneous voice or video calls. Therefore, the second call won't be queued; it will either show as missed or the caller may receive a message that you're unavailable at the moment.\n   - **User Experience:** From your perspective, you won't receive any direct notification about the second caller until you finish your ongoing call. The second caller won't see an explicit \"busy\" status, but the inability to connect effectively communicates that you're currently occupied.\n\n3. **Post-Call Availability:**\n   - Once you end the initial call, the second caller can attempt to call you again, at which point they'll be able to reach you if you're available.\n\n**Summary:**\nWhile WhatsApp doesn't explicitly display a \"busy\" status to callers, attempting to reach you during an active WhatsApp call effectively results in the caller being unable to connect until you're free, similar to encountering a busy status.\n\n**Note:** WhatsApp's features may evolve over time, so it's always a good idea to keep the app updated to benefit from the latest functionalities and user experience improvements.\n\nWhen you\u2019re already on a WhatsApp call, a second person calling you will see that you\u2019re busy or unavailable\u2014their call won\u2019t connect until you finish your current call.",
